            "id": "7e91a9fd5c9846edb3691",
            "questionText": "A 12 V car battery with an internal resistance of 0.05 \\(\\Omega\\) powers two headlights connected in parallel. Each headlight has a resistance of 2 \\(\\Omega\\). Calculate the current flowing through each headlight.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "aff43c575c96410ea6d0b",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by determining the effective resistance of the two headlights connected in parallel. To do this, you need to identify the correct formula for combining resistors in parallel. Which one of the following formulas identifies the relationship for parallel resistors?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "9fa1c405-382b-4536-a722-8d3db2c9d128"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\frac{1}{R_T} = \\frac{1}{R_1} + \\frac{1}{R_2}$!$",
